        {
            "review_id": "226549223",
            "steam_id": "76561198054897327",
            "playtime_minutes": 489,
            "voted_up": false,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.4761904776096344,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "What a disappointment. Played this with one other person the whole time.\n\nPros:\nDashing and throwing items is great\nPrecise handling (unlike PlateUp!)\nLevels are uniquely enjoyable with themes and movement that keeps the gameplay new\n\nCons:\nStory - who cares\nMap Movement - just a waste of time\nDifficulty - The first go around was very easy, even for 2 first time players to the series. We beat every level on the first or second try, not a brag, it just wasn't that hard and we didn't have to make that many adjustments to get the high score each time. I was happy to see there's essentially a new game + once you beat every level. Instead of putting all the skills you've learned to the test you just make a ton of food and throw it on the floor then start the clock. This was the deciding factor for me to give a thumbs down, I get that you may want to make the first go through easy for some gamers but the second go around should challenge you to better yourself at the game mechanics and order of operations you use in order to complete dishes. After playing the first level again in new game + with my friend numerous times and really optimizing each process we still were not even close to the par score. We watched a video of how 2 others beat the level and after seeing them just make food and throw it on the ground before starting the clock I realized that the whole experience is empty. The first go around is way too easy and the second go around isn't even hard, you just bypass the way to play the game with a method that feels like an exploit."
        },
